misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes the trip cost is computed as distance divided by miles-per-gallon, multiplied by price-per-gallon, and that Java will evaluate this arithmetic as expected for doubles.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap: this matches the correct execution model and formula. With all operands as doubles, Java performs floating-point division/multiplication and concatenates the result into the output string correctly.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No error; produces correct numeric result for the sample input (155 / 23.5 * 5.2 = 34.297872340425535).
